The South African Weather Service has issued a warning to expect severe thunderstorms across the northern parts of the country on Thursday. Storms are expected on the highveld of Mpumalanga, as well as the northern and north-eastern parts of Gauteng. The western parts of Limpopo could also expect heavy thunderstorms, said the weather service. There is a 60% chance of showers in the north of Pretoria and a 30% chance of rain for the rest of Gauteng.